reviews.review_text: My first Dead show I just graduated from high school and finally made it to my first Dead show. Pretty decent mid-80s show with some nice surprises.  It was mid-summer and the crowd was pumped.  Great party, Jerry sounds strong and the band is sounding pretty tight.  Nice versions of Terrapin and Wharf Rat. The Revolution-> Brokedown encore is also strong.  Thanks for posting.

My first show! Funny how long ago , the strange trip -good sound good night. They stopped doing the Lost Sailor •Saint of Circumstance combo soon after. Bob in a pink Alligator T-Shirt ( classic) . The encore - Jerry Garcia " Hello - sounded good didn't it . We all started playin .... Blah blah blah . "The Throwin Stones • Turn on Your Lovelight is great. The Terrapin Station is fabulous as is the whole first set. Woman are Smarter ( ManSmart Woman are Smarter) second set opener is a treat.Crazy Fingers!!!!             Set 1

Jack Straw-> It Must Have Been The Roses, Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Cassidy, Big Railroad Blues, Promised Land

Set 2

Women Are Smarter-> Crazy Fingers-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E:Revolution-> E: Brokedown Palace

3.9 stars This Coyote et al. AUD recording is my favorite of all those currently available here for this show. It is a touch tinny, and the high end is a bit too high, but this is easily fixed with some minor EQing. 

The first set is the better of the two, with an excellent Cassidy and good performances of everything else. The second set is more erratic, with Saint being the highlight, and Drums lets the side down with some technical problems that are hard to ignore. The encore is a truly quintessential Grateful Dead moment, with Revolution falling apart from the beginning, barely saved from sucking by an awesome Garcia solo, and Brokedown chopped up into pieces and then glued back together in completely the wrong order, but sounding good anyway, with stellar vocal harmonies. It sounds like they had fun playing it, and that counts for something at a Dead show.

The Iglo - or Golf Ball ? This was one show out of the entire '85 summer tour that was indoors --- Awsome show - the Cassidy rocked !!  The Sailor -> Saint was a blessing ... the sound was just OK, but if you were in the first few rows, it was beautiful !
